# Create folder and files
mkdir HMOSHIELD-Hedera-Hackathon && cd HMOSHIELD-Hedera-Hackathon

# Create all files (copy-paste one by one from above)
# Or use this script (paste all at once):

cat > .env.example << 'EOF'
OPERATOR_ID=0.0.123456
OPERATOR_KEY=302e0201...yourED25519privateKey...
NETWORK=testnet
EOF

cat > package.json << 'EOF'
{
  "name": "hmoshield-hedera-hackathon",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "HMOSHIELD prototype for DoraHacks African Hackathon – DLT Operations track",
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node index.js"
  },
  "author": "HMOSHIELD Team",
  "license": "MIT",
  "dependencies": {
    "@hashgraph/sdk": "^2.30.0",
    "dotenv": "^16.4.5"
  }
}
EOF

cat > README.md << 'EOF'
# HMOSHIELD – Hedera Hackathon Prototype

**Goal:** Demonstrate ShieldCoin (SHC) creation, claims validation via smart contract, and fraud alerts via HCS on Hedera Testnet.

## Quick Start

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd HMOSHIELD-Hedera-Hackathon
npm install
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your Hedera Testnet operator ID & private key
npm start
